        "description": "Play the classic and very popular game called chess! The simple interface supports smooth browser gaming on both PC and mobile.\n\nThe chess comes from the Persian game Shatranj. It was also a strategic board game that spread to Europe through the Arabs. Modern chess as we know them today has replaces Shatranj because it is faster.\n\nOver time, chess has become a regular professional sport from home entertainment. In 1924 the International Chess Federation (FIDE) was founded in France. The aim of the game is an inevitable attack on the king called mat. There is no element of randomness in chess, everything is decided by the knowledge and skills of the players.<br>\n <br>\nChess was played on the game boards, but in the second half of the 20th century with the new technology (computers), chess fought its way on the screen. Millions of laymen play against each other in online matches and refine their strategies. Artificial intelligence is often used, because it can be challenging a lot. You can play against AI today as well. Set the difficulty from easy to master. Train your strategy. Have fun."
